<eesti>Turuj&auml;relevalve k&auml;igus tuvastatud ohtlikest toodetest v&auml;lisriigi teavitamise tingimused ja kord (1) </eesti>
<inglise>Conditions and Procedure for Notifying Foreign States of Dangerous Products Detected in Course of Market Supervision (1) </inglise>
<eesti>Vabariigi Valitsuse 8. veebruari 2000. a m&auml;&auml;rus nr 39 </eesti>
<inglise>Government of the Republic Regulation No. 39 of 8 February 2000 </inglise>
<eesti>(RT I 2000, 11, 71), </eesti>
<inglise>(RT* I 2000, 11, 71), </inglise>
<eesti>j&otilde;ustunud 20. veebruaril 2000. a. </eesti>
<inglise>entered into force 20 February 2000. </inglise>
<eesti>M&auml;&auml;rus kehtestatakse "Toote ohutuse seaduse" (RT I 1998, 40, 613; 1999, 82, 753) &sect; 11 l&otilde;ike 2 alusel v&auml;lisriigi teavitamiseks turuj&auml;relevalve k&auml;igus tuvastatud ohtlikest toodetest. </eesti>
<inglise>This Regulation is established on the basis of subsection 11 (2) of the Product Safety Act (RT I 1998, 40, 613; 1999, 82, 753) for notifying foreign states of dangerous products detected in the course of market supervision. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Teavitamise korra kohaldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Application of notification procedure </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turuj&auml;relevalve k&auml;igus tuvastatud ohtlikest toodetest teavitamise korda (edaspidi teavitamise kord) kohaldatakse v&auml;lisriigi teavitamisel tootest, mille ohtlikkus tuvastati Eesti territooriumil turuj&auml;relevalve k&auml;igus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The procedure for giving notification of dangerous products detected in the course of market supervision (hereinafter notification procedure) applies upon notifying foreign states of products which are identified as dangerous in the course of market supervision within the territory of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse kohaselt teavitatakse Euroopa Liidu liikmesriike, assotsieerunud riike v&otilde;i riike, kellega on s&otilde;lmitud vastav leping (edaspidi v&auml;lisriik). </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The member states of the European Union, associated countries, and states with whom a corresponding agreement is entered into (hereinafter foreign states) shall be notified pursuant to this Regulation. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esolevat teavitamise korda ei kohaldata juhul, kui selline teavitamine on ette n&auml;htud ja reguleeritud teistes &otilde;igusaktides. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) This notification procedure is not applied if such notification is prescribed in and regulated by other legislation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>Teabe edastaja </eesti>
<inglise>Notifying bodies </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turuj&auml;relevalve k&auml;igus tuvastatud ohtlikust tootest teavitab v&auml;lisriiki Tarbijakaitseamet. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Consumer Protection Board shall notify foreign states of dangerous products detected in the course of market supervision. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teised seadustes ja turuj&auml;relevalveasutuste p&otilde;him&auml;&auml;rustes s&auml;testatud korras turuj&auml;relevalvet teostavad ametid ja inspektsioonid on kohustatud regulaarselt vahetama omavahel informatsiooni nende poolt turuj&auml;relevalve k&auml;igus tuvastatud ohtlikust tootest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Other boards and inspectorates which exercise market supervision pursuant to the procedure provided by Acts and the statutes of market supervisory authorities shall regularly exchange information concerning dangerous products detected by them in the course of market supervision. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud informatsioon edastatakse kohe ka Tarbijakaitseametile. </eesti>
<inglise>Such information shall also be immediately communicated to the Consumer Protection Board. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Teavitamise tingimused </eesti>
<inglise>Conditions for notification </inglise>
<eesti>(1) V&auml;lisriiki tuleb teavitada turuj&auml;relevalve k&auml;igus tuvastatud, tarbijale kasutamiseks etten&auml;htud v&otilde;i tarbija poolt t&otilde;en&auml;oliselt kasutatavast ohtlikust tootest, v&auml;lja arvatud "Toote ohutuse seaduse" &sect; 1 l&otilde;ikes 4 loetletud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Except in the cases listed in subsection 1 (4) of the Consumer Protection Act, foreign states shall be notified of dangerous products detected in the course of market supervision, intended by consumers or likely to be used by consumers. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) V&auml;lisriiki teavitatakse ohtlikust tootest juhul, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Foreign states shall be notified of a dangerous product if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) on ilmnenud t&otilde;sine ja otsene oht tarbija tervisele ja turvalisusele, </eesti>
<inglise>1) a serious and immediate risk to the health and safety of consumers becomes evident, </inglise>
<eesti>2) turuj&auml;relevalveasutused on tarvitusele v&otilde;tnud v&otilde;i otsustanud tarvitusele v&otilde;tta meetmeid selle toote turustamise piiramiseks v&otilde;i turult k&otilde;rvaldamiseks ja </eesti>
<inglise>2) the market supervisory authorities have adopted or decided to adopt measures entailing restrictions on the marketing of the product or requiring its withdrawal from the market, and </inglise>
<eesti>3) toote turustamine ulatub v&otilde;i v&otilde;ib ulatuda v&auml;ljapoole Eesti territooriumi. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the marketing of the product extends or may extend beyond the territory of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) V&auml;lisriiki v&otilde;ib vajadusel teavitada ohtlikust tootest ka siis, kui turuj&auml;relevalveasutus ei ole veel otsustanud ohtliku toote suhtes tarvitusele v&otilde;etavate vajalike meetmete osas. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If necessary, foreign states may also be notified of a dangerous product if a market supervisory authority has not yet decided on the necessary measures to be adopted concerning the dangerous product. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva teavitamise korra j&auml;rgi ei teavitata v&auml;lisriiki tootest, mille puhul on kahtlus, et see v&otilde;ib p&otilde;hjustada ohtu tarbija tervisele pikema aja m&ouml;&ouml;dudes ja mille suhtes teostatakse uurimisi ja katsetusi v&otilde;imalike tehniliste normide v&otilde;i standardite kehtestamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Foreign countries shall not be notified pursuant to this notification procedure of products which are suspected of involving long-term risks to the health of consumers and which are being studied and tested in order to establish technical regulations or standards. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui ohtlikuks osutunud toote suhtes tarvitusele v&otilde;etud meetmete hulgas n&auml;hakse ette &otilde;igusakti t&auml;iendamist tehnilise normiga v&otilde;i tehnilist normi sisaldava &otilde;igusakti v&auml;ljat&ouml;&ouml;tamist, teavitatakse sellest vastavalt Vabariigi Valitsuse 25. juuni 1999. a m&auml;&auml;ruses nr 201 "Tehnilist normi sisaldava &otilde;igusakti ja v&auml;lislepingu eeln&otilde;ust teavitamise korra kinnitamine ning teabevahetust koordineeriva asutuse m&auml;&auml;ramine" (RT I 1999, 57, 600) s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If the measures adopted with regard to a dangerous product prescribe the amendment of a piece of legislation by adding a technical regulation or the drafting of a piece of legislation containing a technical regulation, notification shall be given thereof pursuant to the requirements provided for in Government of the Republic Regulation No. 201 of 25 June 1999 "Approval of Procedure for Giving Notification of Draft Legislation and Draft International Agreements Containing Technical Regulations and Appointment of Authority Co-ordinating Information Exchange" (RT I 1999, 57, 600). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Teavitamise korraldamiseks vajaliku teabe kogumine </eesti>
<inglise>Collection of information necessary for organisation of notification </inglise>
<eesti>(1) P&auml;rast turuj&auml;relevalve k&auml;igus tarbijale t&otilde;sist ja otsest ohtu kujutava toote tuvastamist v&otilde;tab turuj&auml;relevalveasutus nii ruttu kui v&otilde;imalik &uuml;hendust k&otilde;nesoleva toote tootja v&otilde;i levitajaga, et saada temalt vajalikke selgitusi ja t&auml;ielikku teavet toote kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) As soon as possible after a product involving a serious and immediate risk to consumers is detected in the course of market supervision, the market supervisory authority shall contact the producer or distributor of the product concerned in order to obtain necessary explanations and complete information concerning the product. </inglise>
<eesti>Turuj&auml;relevalveasutusel tuleb kiiresti hankida v&otilde;imalikult palju teavet toote ja sellega seonduva ohu kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>The market supervisory authority shall rapidly obtain as much information as possible concerning the product and the risk involved. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Oma p&auml;devuse piires tegutsevad teised turuj&auml;relevalveasutused edastavad kiiresti Tarbijakaitseametile nende poolt tuvastatud ohtliku toote ja sellega seonduva ohu kohta kogutud teabe, teatades &uuml;htlasi, millised meetmed on toote suhtes tarvitusele v&otilde;etud v&otilde;i kavatsetakse tarvitusele v&otilde;tta, v&otilde;i tehes ettepanekud vajalike meetmete tarvitusele v&otilde;tmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Other market supervisory authorities acting within the limits of their competence shall rapidly communicate any information collected concerning a dangerous product detected by them and the risk involved to the Consumer Protection Board, and provide details concerning the measures adopted or intended to be adopted concerning the product or make proposals for the adoption of necessary measures. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Tuvastatud ohtliku toote kohta v&auml;lisriigile edastatav teave </eesti>
<inglise>Information to be communicated to foreign states concerning detected dangerous products </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tarbijakaitseamet edastab tuvastatud ohtliku toote kohta v&auml;lisriigile j&auml;rgmise teabe: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Consumer Protection Board shall communicate the following information concerning a detected dangerous product to foreign states: </inglise>
<eesti>1) vajalik teave toote identifitseerimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) information necessary to identify the product; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tootega seonduva ohu kirjeldus, kaasa arvatud nende katsetuste ja anal&uuml;&uuml;side tulemused, mis on olulised tootega seonduva ohu hindamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a description of the risk involved, including the results of any tests or analyses which are relevant to assessing the level of risk involved; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teave tarvitusele v&otilde;etud v&otilde;i tarvitusele v&otilde;tta otsustatud meetmete kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) information concerning the measures which have been or will be adopted; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teave toote levitajate turustusahela kohta, kui selline teave on olemas. </eesti>
<inglise>4) information concerning the supply chains of the distributors of the product, where such information is possible. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud teave edastatakse v&auml;lisriigile kirjalikult k&otilde;ige suuremat operatiivsust v&otilde;imaldavate sidevahendite abil. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The information specified in subsection (1) shall be communicated to foreign states in writing by the most expeditious means of communications. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;lisriigilt saabunud teabe vastuv&otilde;tmine </eesti>
<inglise>Receipt of information from foreign states </inglise>
<eesti>(1) V&auml;lisriik saadab teabe tema territooriumil turuj&auml;relevalve k&auml;igus tuvastatud, tarbija tervisele ja turvalisusele t&otilde;sist ja otsest ohtu kujutava toote kohta Tarbijakaitseametile. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Foreign states communicate information concerning products which are detected within their territories in the course of market supervision and which involve direct and immediate risk to the health and safety of consumers to the Consumer Protection Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tarbijakaitseamet kontrollib v&auml;lisriigilt saadud teabes kirjeldatud toote v&otilde;imalikku turustamist Eesti territooriumil v&otilde;i edastab selle teabe kontrollimiseks p&auml;devale turuj&auml;relevalveasutusele ning vajadusel teavitab avalikkust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Consumer Protection Board shall verify whether a product concerning which information is received from a foreign state is marketed in the territory of Estonia or forward the information to a competent market supervisory authority for verification and, if necessary, notify the public. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) V&auml;lisriigilt saadud teabe alusel Eesti territooriumil tuvastatud ohtliku toote suhtes teeb turuj&auml;relevalveasutus otsuse vastavalt "Toote ohutuse seaduse" &sect; 9 l&otilde;ikele 5. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A decision concerning a dangerous product detected in the territory of Estonia on the basis of information received from a foreign state shall be made by a market supervisory authority pursuant to subsection 9 (5) of the Product Safety Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tarbijakaitseamet teavitab v&auml;lisriiki temalt saadud teabe alusel Eesti territooriumil tuvastatud ohtliku toote suhtes tarvitusele v&otilde;etud meetmetest. (1) Euroopa &Uuml;henduse direktiiv 92/59/EM&Uuml; (E&Uuml;T L 228, 29.06.1992, lk 24) </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Consumer Protection Board shall notify a foreign state of the measures adopted concerning a dangerous product detected in the territory of Estonia on the basis of information received from the foreign state. </inglise>
